			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">For NaCl to work in the seccomp sandbox on x86-32, the sandbox will have to 
allow the modify_ldt() system call, which is used for setting up x86 
segmentation.

While it should be harmless to allow this syscall in renderer processes, we 
would want to disallow it to be on the safe side.  This would require making 
the seccomp sandbox's policies more configurable.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-04-02T04:05:59.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-05-10T15:44:06.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>WontFix</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
